                        <h2 class="post-title-2"><a href="http://ivo.co.za/2014/06/06/on-energy-environment-and-regulatory-independence/" title="Permanent Link to On energy, environment, and regulatory independence">
                On energy, environment, and regulatory independence                </a></h2>
            <div style="clear: both;"></div>

		
            <div class="featured-thumb-wrapper">
			<a href="http://ivo.co.za/2014/06/06/on-energy-environment-and-regulatory-independence/" title="Permanent Link to On energy, environment, and regulatory independence">
				<img src="http://ivo.co.za/wp-content/uploads/et_temp/plug-16450_85x85.png" alt='On energy, environment, and regulatory independence' width='85px' height='85px' />			</a>
		</div>        
	    		
			<div>
            I recently had the pleasure of participating in a live radio debate about whether shale gas threatens our water resources. Afterwards, I was accused of making a personal attack on one of my debate opponents. This disappointed me, because I had intended the attack to be entirely professional.            </div>
                <a href="http://ivo.co.za/2014/06/06/on-energy-environment-and-regulatory-independence/" rel="bookmark" class="readmore" title="Permanent Link to On energy, environment, and regulatory independence">
