                        <h2 class="post-title-2"><a href="http://ivo.co.za/2014/05/07/its-about-who-you-dont-vote-for/" title="Permanent Link to It’s about who you don’t vote for">
                It’s about who you don’t vote for                </a></h2>
            <div style="clear: both;"></div>

		
        		
			<div>
            I spent several columns in the last few weeks pondering who most deserves my vote, and why. Several parties have attractions, but none were an obvious fit for an advocate of individual liberty and free markets. I realised that it really is a Morton’s Fork – no matter who you vote for, they’re all power-hungry thieves. But there is a rational way out.            </div>
                <a href="http://ivo.co.za/2014/05/07/its-about-who-you-dont-vote-for/" rel="bookmark" class="readmore" title="Permanent Link to It’s about who you don’t vote for">
    read more 
    </a>
