        <span class="headings">Bio</span>
<div class="home-sidebar-box">			<div class="textwidget"><p><img width="230" class="aligncenter" src="http://ivo.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Ivo-Vegter-Website-Avatar.png" /></p>
<p>Ivo Vegter is a columnist and the author of Extreme Environment, a book on environmental exaggeration and how it harms emerging economies. He approaches issues from the perspective of individual liberty and free markets. </p>
<p>He grew up in the deep south of Johannesburg, and learnt his politics reading the Weekly Mail and Vrye Weekblad at Wits University during the early years of the country's transition to democracy. </p>
<p>He recently left the city for the lower cost of living of Knysna, where he continues to write about everything under the sun. </p>
</div>
